Prerequisites and Installation

1.	Docker
	https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/
	a.	Prerequisites
		i.	Windows
			1.	Windows 10 Pro-Enterprise (won’t work on home version)
			2.	Hyper-v installed and running
				a.	Check virtualization under ‘performance’ in task manager
				b.	If it’s not enabled, enable it by searching “Turn Windows features on or off”
	b.	Download Docker Desktop installer (from docker hub)
		i.	https://hub.docker.com/editions/community/docker-ce-desktop-windows/
		ii.	Different options (Choose “Linux containers”)
		iii.	Once installed, open powershell
			1.	Check version (docker --version)
			2.	Run hello-world (docker run hello-world)
				a.	Verify that it worked
					i.	It will download and display a message form docker
			3.	Pull an image of the Ubuntu OS (docker run --interactive --tty ubunto bash)
				a.	Exit (exit)
